<td class="description">
Transmission electron micrograph of a myelinated axon. The myelin layer (concentric) surrounds the axon of a neurone, showing cytoplasmathic organs inside. Generated and deposited into the public domain by the Electron Microscopy Facility at Trinity College.</td>
</tr>

